---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
import { AUTHOR, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Person',
  name: AUTHOR.name,
  jobTitle: AUTHOR.title,
  url: `https://mykytashaban.dev`,
  sameAs: [AUTHOR.github, AUTHOR.linkedin],
  address: {
    '@type': 'PostalAddress',
    addressLocality: 'Wroclaw',
    addressCountry: 'PL',
  },
};
---

<Layout
  title={`About — ${SITE_TITLE}`}
  description={`${AUTHOR.name} is a Frontend Performance Engineer based in Wroclaw, Poland. Focused on Core Web Vitals, e-commerce performance, and making the web faster.`}
  pageJsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <p>
    I'm Mykyta Shaban, a senior frontend developer based in Wroclaw, Poland.
    Originally from Ukraine.
  </p>

  <p>
    I've spent several years building frontend applications with React and
    modern JavaScript. My current focus is web performance — understanding what
    makes pages slow, how to measure it properly, and how to fix it in a way
    that actually holds up in production.
  </p>

  <p>
    My day job involves working on a checkout SDK — code that runs inside other
    companies' e-commerce sites. Checkout is one of the most
    performance-sensitive surfaces on the web. A slow checkout costs money,
    directly and measurably. That context made performance feel concrete rather
    than theoretical.
  </p>

  <h2>What I focus on</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Core Web Vitals</strong> — measurement, diagnosis, and improvement of
      LCP, CLS, and INP
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>JavaScript performance</strong> — bundle analysis, parse time, runtime
      bottlenecks
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>E-commerce and checkout</strong> — where performance has direct business
      impact
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Rendering patterns</strong> — SSR, streaming, islands architecture,
      partial hydration
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Real user monitoring</strong> — field data, percentiles, understanding
      real-world conditions
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>This blog</h2>

  <p>
    I write to document what I learn. Clear notes from real work, not textbook
    theory. If something helped me understand a concept or fix a problem in
    production, it's worth writing about.
  </p>

  <h2>Connect</h2>

  <p>
    Find me on <a href={AUTHOR.github} target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'
      >GitHub</a
    >,
    <a href={AUTHOR.linkedin} target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'
      >LinkedIn</a
    >. For direct contact: <a href={`mailto:${AUTHOR.email}`}>{AUTHOR.email}</a
    >.
  </p>
</Layout>
